# Deep Competitive Analysis: B2B Jewellery Inventory & Order Management Platform

> Researched April 2026 | Sources: Official websites, Capterra, G2, SoftwareSuggest, Sourceforge, GoodFirms

---

## Section 1: Your Product — "The Platform" (j.md)

### Core Identity
A **single-owner B2B Jewellery Sales & Order Enablement Platform**. A manufacturer or wholesaler runs this platform privately for their own 100+ dealer network. Dealers log in, browse a visual catalogue, build carts, and punch orders. The owner approves orders, tracks inventory, and manages the business through analytics.

### What Makes It Unique (Before Any Comparison)
1. **Dealer-first UX** — Designed for the buying experience, not the billing experience.
2. **Not multi-tenant** — This is a private, single-owner platform. It is NOT a marketplace or SaaS shared across jewellers.
3. **No GST / Tax accounting** — Intentionally out of scope. Creates a quotation-only model to stay frictionless.
4. **Dynamic schema** — Custom fields engine means one platform can serve a Kundan wholesaler and a Diamond solitaire manufacturer with completely different data models.
5. **AI-first discovery** — Visual similarity search and auto-tagging solve real problems for dealers and workforce respectively.
6. **B2B e-commerce DNA** — Cart, checkout, order approval, order history. None of the competitors think this way.

---

## Section 2: Competitor PRDs

---

### 2.1 Jwelly ERP (by MMI Softwares Pvt. Ltd.)

**Website:** https://jwelly.com | https://jwelly.ai  
**HQ:** Mathura, Uttar Pradesh  
**Tagline:** "Best Jewellery Business Software in India"  
**Rating:** 4.7/5 (455 reviews, self-reported)  
**Operating Systems:** Windows, Android, iOS, Mac OS  
**Deployment:** Client-server (Windows) + Cloud-hosted option  

#### Product Vision
A full-spectrum ERP for the entire jewellery trade—from a single retail counter to a multi-branch chain, wholesale house, manufacturing unit, bullion trader, or money lender. It is the most feature-complete platform of the three competitors.

#### Target Segments
| Segment | Focus |
|---|---|
| Retail Showroom | POS, Billing, CRM, Schemes |
| Wholesale | Bulk orders, Party accounts, Metal trading |
| Manufacturing | Karigar, Job work, Production |
| Bullion Trading | Metal rate-based transactions |
| Girvi / Money Lending | Pledge-based gold loan management |

#### Full Feature Breakdown

**INVENTORY MANAGEMENT**
- Real-time stock tracking by weight, purity, piece, batch, tag, and carat
- Barcode + RFID integration for tagging every item
- Multi-location / multi-branch inventory under one dashboard
- Low stock alerts
- Stock-by-image filtering (AI visual search — see AI section)
- Bulk stock counting (physical to digital audit)
- Weight configuration: Gross, Net, Fine, Making Weight

**SALES & BILLING (RETAIL/POS)**
- Lightning-fast POS screen optimized for showroom counter speed
- Barcode scan-to-bill
- GST-compliant invoices (CGST, SGST, IGST)
- Tax Invoice, Estimate, Quotation, Approval
- E-invoicing (IRN generation)
- Multiple payment modes (cash, card, UPI, gold tendering)
- Discount, scheme, and coupon application
- Returns and exchanges
- Bill sharing via WhatsApp / SMS

**WHOLESALE MODULE (One-Screen Entry)**
- Single screen for: Sales, Sale Returns, Purchases, Metal Receipts, Cash Receipts, Bhav (gold rate) Fixation, Stock Transfer — all in one view
- Bulk inventory in poly or box format
- Customer-wise profit report (adjusting for metal rate, wastage, labour)
- Automatic wastage and labour rate picking based on customer history
- Party ledger sharing via WhatsApp
- Mobile app for fast billing at exhibitions

**MANUFACTURING MODULE**
- Karigar (artisan) job assignment and tracking
- Material issuance and return tracking
- Fine weight / net gold tracking per job
- Job-wise and setting-wise production stages (casting, polishing, setting)
- Payroll automation from job completion
- Gold balance ledger per karigar
- Galai (refining / gold loss) tracking
- Diamond processing module
- Job sheet generation

**FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING**
- Full double-entry accounting: Ledger, P&L, Balance Sheet, Trial Balance
- Auto-calculation of TDS / TCS
- GSTR-1, GSTR-3B report generation
- Tally integration (export to Tally format)
- HSN/SAC code support
- Multi-currency (for export / NRI dealings)

**GIRVI — GOLD LOAN / MONEY LENDING**
- Pledge item registration with photo
- Interest auto-calculation (flat / reducing basis)
- Due date reminders
- Pledge release / forfeit workflows
- Agreement printing

**CRM & CUSTOMER MANAGEMENT**
- Customer profiles with purchase history
- Birthday / anniversary reminders (automated SMS/WhatsApp)
- Loyalty points and digital kitty/chit fund schemes
- Customer-facing mobile app (for loyalty transparency)
- SMS / Email / WhatsApp marketing campaigns

**MULTI-BRANCH & OPERATIONS**
- Centralized owner dashboard across all branches
- Branch-wise P&L
- Inter-branch stock transfer
- User roles and permissions

**OWNER APP**
- Monitor business in real-time from phone
- Check sales, stock levels, customer activity
- Alerts for reorder points, scheme renewals, birthdays

**JWELLY AI MODULE** (jwelly.ai — separate product under same company)
- **Image Recognition / Stock Filter by Image:** Search inventory using a product photo
- **Smart Catalog:** Converts raw product photos into professional studio images (background removal, enhancement, watermarking) — bulk processing
- **Data Analytics:** Sales analysis for smart purchase planning
- **Smart Alerts:** Voice-activated alerts for critical tasks
- **Voice Activated Operations:** Billing, reports, accounts via voice commands
- **Customer Live:** (photo-to-studio-image conversion for catalogues)

**PRICING**
- No public pricing; custom quote model
- Based on: number of outlets, modules selected, number of users
- Typically annual licensing fee (perpetual + AMC model)

**GAPS / WEAKNESSES**
- No true dealer-facing self-service portal with cart + order punch
- No dynamic/custom field schema engine
- No vector-based visual similarity search for dealers ("find me something like this")
- No AI auto-tagging on product upload
- Heavy complexity — overwhelming for new users
- No demand forecasting (predictive analytics)
- No per-product-image embedding for discovery
- The Jwelly AI visual search is an internal staff tool, not a dealer-facing discovery tool

