## Section 3: Exhaustive Feature-by-Feature Comparison

### 3.1 Core Platform & Architecture

| Dimension | Your Platform | Jwelly ERP | SwarnaVyapar | JewelMaker |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Primary Use Case** | B2B order enablement (Wholesaler → Dealer) | Full ERP (Retail + Wholesale + Mfg) | Retail showroom ops | All-in-one (Retail + Wholesale + Mfg) |
| **Deployment Type** | Cloud SaaS (Next.js/PostgreSQL) | Windows client-server + Cloud option | Cloud SaaS | Cloud SaaS + Offline |
| **Multi-tenancy** | No (single owner, N dealers) | Yes (multi-branch) | Yes (multi-store) | Yes (multi-store) |
| **Offline Support** | No (by design) | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| **Mobile App** | PWA (planned) | Native app (iOS/Android) | Native app | Native app |
| **Tablet Optimized** | Yes (responsive) | Yes | Yes | Yes (tablet catalog) |
| **Tech Stack** | Next.js, PostgreSQL, pgvector, Socket.io | Proprietary Windows/.NET | Modern SaaS (unknown stack) | Unknown (likely PHP/React) |
| **Real-Time Updates** | Yes (WebSockets/SSE) | No (polling) | Unknown | No |

