## Section 4: Strategic Gap Analysis

### 4.1 What Exists (Solved Problems)
| Problem | Best Solver Today |
|---|---|
| GST billing & tax compliance | Jwelly, JewelMaker, SwarnaVyapar |
| Karigar / production management | Jwelly, JewelMaker |
| Retail POS / fast billing | Jwelly, SwarnaVyapar |
| Inventory tracking by weight/purity | All three |
| Gold Loan (Girvi) management | Jwelly, SwarnaVyapar |
| Barcode / RFID tagging | Jwelly, JewelMaker |
| Basic B2B catalogue sharing | JewelMaker (WhatsApp), Jwelly (Mobile) |
| Voice-activated operations | Jwelly AI, SwarnaVyapar |
| AI invoice scanning | SwarnaVyapar |

### 4.2 What Does NOT Exist (Your Opportunity)
| Unsolved Problem | Your Solution |
|---|---|
| **Dealer cannot self-browse and self-order** without calling the owner or WhatsApping | Dealer Portal with cart + order punch |
| **No order approval workflow** (owner approves, rejects, partially approves per line item) | Owner Order Management with workflow |
| **No real-time catalogue** showing live stock as dealers browse | WebSocket-powered live inventory |
| **"Find something like this" visual search for dealers** | AI Visual Similarity Search (CLIP + pgvector) |
| **Auto-tagging on product upload saves hours** of manual entry | GPT-4o Vision auto-suggest tags/category |
| **Dynamic custom fields** so platform works for any jewellery niche | Dynamic Schema Engine (JSONB) |
| **Dealer-level analytics** — who's buying, what, when, who's inactive | Dealer Intelligence Module |
| **Lost demand tracking** — who tried to order an out-of-stock item | Out-of-Stock Impact report |
| **Product collections / campaigns** (Diwali 2026 collection) | Collections Module |
| **Weekly AI business digest** in plain language | AI Business Digest |
| **Natural language order search** for dealers — "show me gold rings under 50g" | NLP Search → Filter |
| **Product description generation** from structured fields + images | 1-click AI Descriptions |
| **Demand forecasting** surfaced proactively to owner dashboard | AI Demand Alerts |

