## Section 6: Competitive Risk Assessment

| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Jwelly adds a dealer-facing portal** | Medium | High | Move fast; build network effects (once dealers onboard, switching cost is high) |
| **JewelMaker deepens their B2B portal** | High | Medium | Your AI features (visual search, auto-tag) create a moat they can't easily replicate |
| **SwarnaVyapar pivots to B2B** | Low | Medium | Their brand is retail; a pivot would confuse their core users |
| **New entrant copies your exact concept** | Medium | High | First-mover + network effects from dealer adoption + proprietary AI pipeline |
| **Owner uses WhatsApp catalogue instead** | High | Medium | Your killer feature is the **order management workflow** + **analytics** — WhatsApp has zero of this |

---

## Section 7: Final Strategic Recommendations

### Build Levers (What Makes You Sticky)
1. **The Dealer Flywheel:** Once dealers are trained to log in and punch orders, they won't want to go back to WhatsApp. The order history, wishlist, and saved preferences create retention.
2. **Owner Analytics Moat:** The dealer leaderboard, inactive dealer alerts, and lost demand tracking give the owner business intelligence they've literally never had before. This creates undeniable value.
3. **Dynamic Schema Moat:** A Kundan wholesaler and a Diamond exporter can both use your platform because they define their own data model. Competitors are locked to fixed schemas.
4. **AI Visual Discovery:** "Show me something like this" is the killer feature for dealers who can't describe what they want. No one in India is doing this in the jewellery B2B space.

### Where You Should NOT Compete
- **GST billing / tax accounting** — Solved well by all three competitors. Don't build it; interop with Tally/Busy instead.
- **Karigar / manufacturing management** — Out of scope, handled by Jwelly/JewelMaker.
- **Barcode/RFID hardware integration** — Unnecessary complexity; your QR/tag is software-only.
- **Gold Loan / Girvi** — Not your user; Jwelly and SwarnaVyapar have this.
- **Voice billing** — Nice to have but not differentiating; focus on your AI priorities first.
